Actually, I'm overcomplicating this. Since both `MockitoAssertionError` and `org.mockito.exceptions.verification.junit.ArgumentsAreDifferent` extend `AssertionError`, the simpler fix is just to catch `AssertionError` instead of the specific JUnit exception. The original code was:

```java
} catch (MockitoAssertionError e) {
    error = handleVerifyException(e);
}
catch (org.mockito.exceptions.verification.junit.ArgumentsAreDifferent e) {
    error = handleVerifyException(e);
}
```

So I can just catch `AssertionError` after `MockitoAssertionError`, since `MockitoAssertionError` extends `AssertionError`, and handle both the same way. This avoids the direct JUnit dependency:

